<h2>Weekly Highlight:  About Livestock Of America</h2>

Livestock Of America (<a href = "https://www.LivestockOfamerica.com" class = "pressbody" target = "_blank">www.LivestockOfAmerica.com</a>) is our first online marketplace and our current focus.
Our target audience is livestock businesses that generate between $1,000 and $250,000 / year. These businesses produce farm-fresh eggs for Huevos Rancheros that make your mouth sing; melt-in-your-mouth steaks that you can eat with a spoon; snuggly softest sweaters, and socks so warm that your tootsies will stay warm on Mt. Everest. And they do most of their business at farmers markets and by word of mouth ... and their profit margins stink.<br /><br />

Our mission is to provide ways for small livestock businesses across America to work better together. LivestockOfAmerica.com is predominately a Business to Business (B2B) website. The site helps connect ranchers to ranchers by giving them a detail-oriented classifieds website where they can easily share all of the information on their animals. For buyers that mean one place where they can make informed buying decisions with confidence.<br /><br />


On <a href = "https://www.LivestockOfamerica.com" class = "pressbody" target = "_blank">www.LivestockOfAmerica.com</a> sellers can list up to 15 types of Livestock (Alpacas, Bison, Cattle, Chickens, Working Dogs, Donkeys, Emus, Goats, Horses, Llamas, Pigs, Rabbits, Sheep, Turkeys, and Yaks). In the future we will also be including listings for Honey Bees, and Hay. <br /><br />

Our goal is to both connect businesses within an industry, but also within an industry group. For instance, we help fiber goat ranchers connect with fiber goat ranchers, but also connect fiber-animal ranchers to fiber goat, alpaca, and sheep ranchers.
The site also has an online product market, and a directory of ranch profiles that include mini-websites for each business.<br /><br />

We have been delighted with the response that <a href = "https://www.LivestockOfamerica.com" class = "pressbody" target = "_blank">www.LivestockOfAmerica.com</a> has received so far, and we are just getting started!<br /><br />



 
